# Search Results Screen — Interaction Spec

Stage 3 → 4 handoff: the search-results screen was identified in Stage 3 CHOICE.md
(v1.excalidraw selected — card-grid layout). Stage 4 enumerates interaction states.

## State Descriptions

### loading
Spinner with "Searching..." label. Debounced 200ms after last keystroke.
AI-powered search: see hax-18 G7 (efficient invocation).

### empty
"No results for '<query>'" with suggestion chips for related topics.
HAX-18 G2: make clear what the AI can search (scope = knowledge base articles).

### error
"Search unavailable" with retry button. If AI search fails, fall back to keyword search.
HAX-18 G16: convey AI limitation ("Using keyword search — AI search is temporarily unavailable").

### success
Card grid of results ranked by relevance. Each card shows: title, excerpt, source, confidence badge.
HAX-18 G11: "Ranked by relevance to your query" label.

## References

- See references/hax-18.md: G2, G7, G11, G16 applied to AI-powered search
- Pattern: Card Stack (Tidwell §3) for results display
- Accessibility: W3C APG Listbox pattern for keyboard navigation of results
